title: American Beauty
overview: A sexually frustrated suburban father has a mid-life crisis after becoming infatuated with his daughter's best friend.

title: Mysterious Skin
overview: A teenage hustler and a young man obsessed with alien abductions cross paths, together discovering a horrible, liberating truth.

title: Il conformista
overview: A weak-willed Italian man becomes a fascist flunky who goes abroad to arrange the assassination of his old teacher, now a political dissident.

title: American History X
overview: A former neo-nazi skinhead tries to prevent his younger brother from going down the same wrong path that he did.

title: La Strada
overview: A care-free girl is sold to a traveling entertainer, consequently enduring physical and emotional pain along the way.

title: Little Women
overview: Jo March reflects back and forth on her life, telling the beloved story of the March sisters - four young women, each determined to live life on her own terms.

title: Blue Velvet
overview: The discovery of a severed human ear found in a field leads a young man on an investigation related to a beautiful, mysterious nightclub singer and a group of psychopathic criminals who have kidnapped her child.

title: Seven Pounds
overview: A man with a fateful secret embarks on an extraordinary journey of redemption by forever changing the lives of seven strangers.

title: The Manchurian Candidate
overview: A former prisoner of war is brainwashed as an unwitting assassin for an international Communist conspiracy.

title: Sling Blade
overview: Karl Childers, a simple man hospitalized since his childhood murder of his mother and her lover, is released to start a new life in a small town.

title: Full Metal Jacket
overview: A pragmatic U.S. Marine observes the dehumanizing effects the Vietnam War has on his fellow recruits from their brutal boot camp training to the bloody street fighting in Hue.

title: The Florida Project
overview: Set over one summer, the film follows precocious six-year-old Moonee as she courts mischief and adventure with her ragtag playmates and bonds with her rebellious but caring mother, all while living in the shadows of Walt Disney World.

title: Black
overview: The cathartic tale of a young woman who can't see, hear or talk and the teacher who brings a ray of light into her dark world.

title: What's Eating Gilbert Grape
overview: A young man in a small Midwestern town struggles to care for his mentally-disabled younger brother and morbidly obese mother while attempting to pursue his own happiness.

title: On Golden Pond
overview: Norman is a curmudgeon with an estranged relationship with his daughter Chelsea. At Golden Pond, he and his wife nevertheless agree to care for Billy, the son of Chelsea's new boyfriend, and a most unexpected relationship blooms.

title: Soorarai Pottru
overview: Nedumaaran Rajangam "Maara" sets out to make the common man fly and in the process takes on the world's most capital intensive industry and several enemies who stand in his way.

title: The Lost Weekend
overview: The desperate life of a chronic alcoholic is followed through a four-day drinking bout.

title: Kis Uykusu
overview: A hotel owner and landlord in a remote Turkish village deals with conflicts within his family and a tenant behind on his rent.

title: The Boy in the Striped Pyjamas
overview: Through the innocent eyes of Bruno, the eight-year-old son of the commandant at a German concentration camp, a forbidden friendship with a Jewish boy on the other side of the camp fence has startling and unexpected consequences.

title: Django Unchained
overview: With the help of a German bounty hunter, a freed slave sets out to rescue his wife from a brutal Mississippi plantation owner.
